parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear cradle bolts can cause the steering wheel to become detached, leading to a loss of steering control, which can result in accidents.
symptoms: The rear cradle bolts snapped while driving
the steering wheel turned 360 degrees non-stop
the vehicle was unable to steer
the subframe rusted
and the engine and rack and pinion collapsed to the ground.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rust and failure of the subframe can cause the engine and rack and pinion to collapse to the ground, leading to a loss of steering control and potential accidents.
symptoms: The subframe was rotten
the vehicle was unsafe to drive
the subframe assembly bolts snapped off on both sides
the steering wheel became detached
and the engine cradle bolts rusted.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the door handles can cause the doors to become stuck, making it difficult or impossible to enter or exit the vehicle, which can be a safety hazard in emergency situations.
symptoms: The outside door handles broke

the door handles locked the consumer out of the vehicle
